Historical and Cultural Contexts
Discuss historical and cultural contexts of music.
Name the historical or cultural background of musical selections learned.
Identify the country or region of musical selections learned.
Recognize characteristics of suitable music for various occasions and traditions.
Describe how musical elements are used in music of our own culture as well as other cultures.
Identify characteristics of music from two different historical periods.
Identify specific compositions as belonging to a particular era in music history.
Recognize the uses of music in everyday life.
Analyze the relationship of a country's traditions and its music.
Identify the historical period during which musical works being studied were composed.
Discuss the relationship of music to the historical period in which it was composed.
Identify prominent musicians in contemporary society.
Identify representative musical works from a variety of cultures and historical periods.
Outline the purpose and function of a particular form of music through history.
Compare and contrast aesthetical aspects of music from different cultural perspectives.
Identify the roles of musicians in society.
Discuss the interrelationships among visual and performing arts disciplines.
Identify ideas and emotions that are expressed through music and other disciplines.
Compare a musical selection with another art form that uses a similar style.
Identify similarities and differences in the meanings of terms common to other arts disciplines.
Describe ways that music is related to another subject area.
Compare a musical style with another art form sharing a similar style or movement.
Discuss similarities among various disciplines of the arts.
Discuss the connections of music to other subject areas.
Discuss connections between the history of one art form or style and another related art form or style.
Describe similarities among different art forms across cultures.
Compare and contrast the origins of music with another core subject area (e.g., history, literature, math).
Critical Thinking
Conduct analyses in music.
Examine music as a way to communicate emotions.
Use music vocabulary to discuss specific works of music.
Identify sounds of different instrument families and voices.
Differentiate between simple musical forms when they are heard.
Describe music as a form of communication.
Use music vocabulary to discuss specific compositions of various styles and cultures.
Recognize specific sounds of instruments and voices.
Recognize and identify specific elements of music (melody, harmony, rhythm, form, timbre).
Identify a musical theme.
Describe and analyze aural examples of music using correct musical terms pertaining to form, meter, rhythm, and basic keys.
Identify the sounds of voices and musical instruments as they are used in musical works.
Discuss the style of a musical selection.
Recognize commonalities in the use of musical elements appearing in music throughout history.
Describe and analyze aural examples of music using correct musical terms pertaining to form, meter, rhythm, basic keys, and simple harmonic progressions.
Compare two contrasting musical works.
Discuss the similarities and differences of artistic styles of music performed.
Formulate and express opinions about musical performances.
Discuss the importance of music in one's own life.
Discuss preferences for musical examples using familiar musical terms.
Draw conclusions about the meaning of the term "classical music."
Discuss the importance of music in our society.
Express personal preference for a specific work using appropriate musical vocabulary.
Identify and discuss copyright issues in music.
Discuss the roles of professional and amateur musicians in society.
Express personal preference for music using appropriate musical terminology.
Debate copyright issues in music.
Develop criteria for high musical quality.
Evaluate constructively the quality of one's performance and the performances of others.
Evaluate how music participation is critical to global culture.
Explain personal preferences for musical styles and pieces, using proper terminology.
Offer an alternative for copyright infringement both for the consumer and the artist.
Develop criteria for high musical quality and apply it to a live musical performance.
Evaluate constructively the quality of one's performance and the performances of others.
Performance
Utilize concepts essential to music.
Sing independently with a clear tone and on pitch.
Identify symbols and notation in music.
Read music notation in simple meters or groupings using a system of symbols, numbers, or letters.
Sing/play independently or in a small ensemble with grade appropriate music, following the cues of a conductor.
Read, notate, and perform meter, rhythm, pitch, dynamics, and tempo using standard music symbols.
Use standard musical notation to sing/play grade appropriate material.
Sing/play independently or in a small ensemble with grade appropriate music, following the cues of a conductor.
Read and notate music symbols (time and key signatures, note values, standard notation symbols for pitch, duration, dynamics, articulation, expression).
Use standard musical notation to sing/play grade appropriate material.
Formulate a method of consistent musical practice.
Perform an appropriate instrumental or vocal part demonstrating rhythm and pitch accuracy, articulation and expression, following the cues from a conductor.
Sight-read simple melodies and rhythms in clefs applicable to the performance medium.
Read music that contains level-appropriate technical demands, expanded ranges, and varied interpretive requirements.
Formulate a method of consistent and efficient musical practice.
Communicate through music, applying artistic concepts, knowledge, and skills.
Identify and perform simple songs from different cultures and genres.
Illustrate group singing and instrumental skills in response to conductor cues.
Echo rhythmic or melodic patterns accurately.
Demonstrate proper behavior for different types of music performances.
Sing in harmony using simple ostinatos, partner songs, descants, and canons.
Perform independently while other students sing or play contrasting parts.
Sing/play accurately with appropriate dynamics, breath control, phrasing, and interpretation.
Discuss and demonstrate the importance of proper concert behavior.
Demonstrate interpersonal skills through working collaboratively and productively with others.
Sing/play accurately, using good breath control, diction, articulation, and posture both alone and in small groups, following the directions of a conductor.
Perform in an ensemble, using appropriate musical technique.
Sing/play expressively with appropriate dynamics and phrasing, considering the intent of the music's creator.
Discuss and demonstrate the importance of proper concert behavior and attire.
Demonstrate interpersonal skills through working collaboratively and productively with others.
Perform in groups, blending vocal/instrumental sounds, matching dynamics, breath control, phrasing, and interpretation in response to the conductor.
Perform in a small ensemble or as a soloist using appropriate musical technique.
Interpret/perform a musical selection, respecting the intent of its creator.
Discuss and demonstrate the importance of proper concert behavior and attire.
Demonstrate interpersonal skills by working collaboratively and productively with others.
Communicate through music with creative expression.
Improvise musical "answers" to given rhythmic and/or melodic phrases.
Sing/play a simple melody following a director.
Move to the beat of music in a prescribed manner.
Create original rhythmic/melodic ostinatos to accompany group performances.
Sing/play a simple melody in a call and response context.
Improvise movement that is stylistically appropriate to music (e.g., free style).
Create a melody when given specific guidelines.
Use a variety of traditional and nontraditional sound sources and electronic media when composing or performing music.
Improvise simple rhythmic and/or melodic accompaniments.
Create an original harmony to accompany a melody.
Perform level-appropriate musical works with expression and technical accuracy.
Improvise rhythmic and melodic variations on given melodies.
